attle, etc.. just trying to get this skill up,.. and in the past week, I have YET to see one skill point increase in Alteration..... so i am still stuck at 223 in alteration...<br><br>I dont even want to talk about divination and or abjuration.. what a joke that is.. I have spent numerous nights sitting around casting inner fire or other abjuration spells just trying to get spell increases, and believe me abjuration is lower than my alteration.. hehe<br><br>I suppose this could be an issue of low wisdom/int.. Krokko is currently at 82 wisdom, and 54 int.. but this is ridiculous...<br><br>Anyone else, Faty or otherwise, having this hard of a time getting your skills up?<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uredgiki.showPublicProfile?language=EN>redgiki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FF0000><CENTER>Beast Lord</FONT></CENTER></span><br>  Posts: 256<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/4/02 1:01:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1765.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about skill increases...</span><hr size=1> Get your wisdom over 100 for your practice sessions, and you will notice a marked increase in your skillups.  If possible, have a whole set of wisdom gear you use for this purpose.  While it doesn't make a big difference over the short term, over the long term it has a pretty big impact on both your mana pool and skill raises.  Good luck!<br><br>I've found, for me, the magic number in most statistics seems to be around 125.  Once I surpass that, the respective skills seem to go up quite satisfactorily. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ucoyoteharts.showPublicProfile?language=EN>coyoteharts</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><CENTER>Beast Lord</CENTER></span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/4/02 1:23:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1765.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about skill increases...</span><hr size=1> I've got two beasties, a Troll on Luclin and an Iksar on Bertoxx.  The troll has out of the box wisdom of 70 and the Iksar maxed at 110.  The difference in fizzle rate and skill increases is HUGE...  my lizard rules the world and my troll is still struggling to get his pet buffed... glad I don't have to do a fizzle check to cast Ripper or Korpseater would just be Korpse....<br>Beastcaller<br>Another thing... contrary to what some folks have said mana regen is heavily wisdom dependent... the same troll's mana regens at about a quarter the iksar, both having approximately the same health regen, the iksar's mana will regen to full before health (also given that I have more Hps than mana, but you get the idea).  <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ukrela.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krela</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/4/02 1:52:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1765.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.unresolved.org/images/everquest/lightn1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about skill increases...</span><hr size=1> Mana regen is based purely on meditation skill + spell or item based modifiers, it is NOT effected by how much wis/int you have. <p><center><font size='1'>Do not meddle in the affairs of Wizards, for they are subtle and quick to anger...<br><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4244'>Persephonne</a> - Sorcerer | <a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4260'>Krela</a> - Templar | Archie - Animist  | Columba - Minstrel </font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/umakaniikaika.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Makani Ikaika</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast Prince</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/5/02 1:05:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1765.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about skill increases...</span><hr size=1> Wis/Int (Whichever is higher) impacts the chance for general skills and casting skills.<br><br>Agi affects defensive skill raises.<br><br>Dex affects offensive skill raises.<br><br>Also, the higher the skill actually is the lower the base chance to gain a skill raise. This is obvious when you work a trade skill. You can blow through the first few dozen with no problem. Sometimes getting 1 raise every check. As you progress you notice fewer and fewer raises per attempt (Barring the gaming worlds worst random number generator in existance.)<br><br>As for mana. The poster above me has partially correct. The only things that affect mana regeneration are:<br><br>Your meditation skill.<br>Wether you are sitting/standing.<br>The amount of Flowing Thought/AA skills you have.<br>And clarity type spells.<br><br>Stats only have an affect on the amount of mana you have. <p><HR><Table><TR><TD>I have wist, sin I couthe meen, that children hath by candle light her shadewe on the wal iseen, and ronne therafter all the night. Bisy aboute the han ben to catchen it with all here might.<BR><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=195112">Makani Ikaika - 48 Beastlord of Terris Thule.</a></td><TD><IMG SRC="http://EQLokahi.homestead.com/files/FlyingGreenDragonEZBoardSignature.gif"></td><TD>And whom they catchen it best wolde wene, sannest it shet out of her sight. The shadewe catchen they ne might, for no lines that they couthe lay. This shadewe I may likne aright to this world and yesterday.<BR><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87954">Lokahi Aloali'i - 60 Bard of Terris Thule.</a></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=1765.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=1765.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1765.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.brentcopeland.com/beastlord/images/messageboard/BL_add_reply2.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=1765.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.threadControl?topicID=1765.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfr